## Week 7: May 12-15 (outreach launches Tue / /services pages live)

### Post 4 — Tuesday, May 12 | Industry Insight

**Topic:** Vendor consolidation math (the demand-gen anchor for outreach)

**English version:**

A 60-unit Budapest apartment building running 5 separate vendors typically pays:

Cleaning: 380,000 HUF / month
HVAC and plumbing (callout-based): 180,000 HUF average / month
General maintenance handyman: 120,000 HUF / month
Security: 220,000 HUF / month
Landscaping: 90,000 HUF seasonal average / month

Direct line item total: 990,000 HUF.

Indirect costs that nobody itemizes:
- Property manager time routing requests: 8-12 hours / week
- Emergency premiums on after-hours callouts: 35% surcharge
- Materials marked up 20-40% by individual contractors
- Compliance gaps when a vendor misses a quarterly audit
- Insurance premium increases when claims trace to vendor confusion

Add those up honestly and the same building runs 1.25M to 1.4M HUF / month all-in.

An integrated FM contract for that property type starts at around 1.02M HUF / month with everything included. Consolidated reporting. Single point of accountability. 24/7 coverage at one rate.

The line items look more expensive on a per-task comparison. The full picture says otherwise.

If you have not run the math on your building lately, run it.

`#FacilityManagement` `#IntegratedFM` `#PropertyOperations` `#Budapest` `#FMOutsourcing`

